Daniel Nicholls has not walked for the last ten years after he hit his head on a sandbank while swimming in the sea off Bondi Beach in Australia in 2003 during what was meant to be a celebration after finishing his exams.

The accident severed his spinal cord and left him with a broken neck, meaning since then he has been unable to walk or feel his legs. He also has limited movement in his arms.

His father told The Times: 'It was the most devastating thing in my life, seeing a fit, healthy, lean, good looking 18 year old boy in bed unable to move.' 

Against the advice of doctors who criticised him for giving the teenager false dreams, Mr Nicholls promised his son he would find a solution.

