The former chef set up the Nicholls Spinal Injury Foundation and managed to raise £1m by producing a cookery book with the help of celebrity chefs including Lawson and Blumenthal.

He set up the foundation to raise funds exclusively for basic medical research in the hope that a way of treating spinal injuries could be found. 

He met Geoffrey Raisman, of University College London, who had previously managed to reverse paralysis in rats by transplant cells from the nose to their spines.

